+/* build #74 (theory A): the engine's FoE DRAM byte-lane is swapped vs the CPU
+ * on our setup. Evidence: our engine MATERIALIZES keys swab32 (scan §4.3,
+ * sip=f844a8c0=swab32(c0a844f8)) while the OEM's engine materializes NETWORK
+ * order (GPON bound entry 5644 sip=A04F680A readable; the OEM HNAPT bind path
