+ * orig key, so that key is engine-written). Same silicon, same operation,
+ * different byte order => a DRAM-port swap config differs (lives outside the
+ * FE block, which compared byte-identical). It also explains every wall:
+ * a BE-written BIND reads back to the engine as swab32 garbage (state bits
+ * 28-29 land in its bits 4-5 = timestamp), so it never honors and rebuilds
+ * its UNBIND on top ("engine owns the state field" was the swap all along).
+ * ppe_swab_all=1: write EVERY table word swab32 (engine then sees an exact
+ * OEM-layout entry) and read engine words back through swab32. Use with
+ * ppe_tuple_swab=0. en75_hwv() is its own inverse (swab32 involution). */
+bool en75_ppe_swab_all;
+static inline u32 en75_hwv(u32 raw)
+{
+	return READ_ONCE(en75_ppe_swab_all) ? swab32(raw) : raw;
+}
